The Nigerian Army, has distributed skill acquisition starter packs, to 53 beneficiaries of Entrepreneurship and Skills Acquisition, at the Gibson Jalo cantonment in Adamawa state. The Commander 23rd Armored Brigade, Brig. Gen Sani Mohammed, at the flag off ceremony, said the  beneficiaries were trained, in-line with the COAS Lt. Gen Tukur Buratai mission to develop their skills for self-reliant. The beneficiaries, who are mainly soldiers spouses and children are trained in tailoring, knitting, sewing, hair dressing, soap making, decoration among others. A beneficiary of the program, Mrs Helen Aci was awarded contract by the Chief of Army Staff to produce a 1000 cold shirt (sweaters), for soldiers. “Mrs Aci has since started producing three different types of the sweaters. “The COAS became interested in her skill work during his visit at the cantonment.” He stressed that the headquarters was ready to order more if the woman produced good product. The locals from neighboring communities, were also trained to improve their means of livelihood from the program. 